					<msContents>
						<summary>

						<p>This might possibly be a record of Kulōttuṅga III. It registers a gift of 28 <hi rend="italic">kāśu</hi> with the interest on which to burn a light during the services in the temple, by one Vāśishṭaṉ Śrīrāghavaṉ Paramēśvaraṉ. The amount was left in deposit with a <hi rend="italic">Śivabrāhmaṇa</hi> of the temple, (with his right of worship as security therefor ?).</p>						

						</summary>
